.TH "libnvme_generate_hostnqn_from_hostid" 9 "libnvme_generate_hostnqn_from_hostid" "April 2026" "libnvme API manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
libnvme_generate_hostnqn_from_hostid \- Generate a host nqn from host identifier
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "char *" libnvme_generate_hostnqn_from_hostid
.BI "(char *hostid "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "hostid" 12
Host identifier
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
If \fIhostid\fP is NULL, the function generates it based on the machine
identifier.
.SH "RETURN"
On success, an NVMe Qualified Name for host identification. This
name is based on the given host identifier. On failure, NULL.
